summary:
Chemical engineer, experience of over 30 years in the oil and gas and 6 in pulp & paper industry. Wide experience, obtained in NL, Syria, Oman, UK. Effective leader of multicultural/diverse teams, ability to communicate with other stakeholders. Expertise:

-	Oil/gas wells, upstream oil/gas processing (also sour gas, LNG, petrochemicals, EOR, steam production & injection);
-	Line management of field O&M teams, lead and direct CSU teams, commissioning completion systems, troubleshooting, production optimization/support; 
-	Facilities Design, in concept, front end and detailed design engineering phases, develop O&M, CSU philosophies; 
-	Integration of new facilities in existing or new organizations (operational costs, ensure availability, plan and execute recruitment and training of staff);
-	In Shell was “Technical Authority Level 2” for production readiness assurance and “HSSE Critical Leader”.

Personal attitude to maintain high standard of work, to work independently and deliver results. No nonsense approach, good at analyzing problems, identifying options and has a good practical sense of what is achievable. Does not get bogged down in details but keeps clear picture of what is necessary to achieve the ultimate goal. Jobs held:

- CSU Manager McDermott the Hague office (diverse projects - offshore, petrochemicals, green steel making, H2 Generation);

- Operations Readiness/CSU Manager for FLUOR, petrochemical project Socar (Steam Cracker, PE derivative );

- ORA Manager (covering O&M input in design, commissioning & start up, flawless project delivery, prepare new assets for operations phase) Abadi floating LNG, Al Karaana Petrochemicals, Kashagan Phase 2 FFD, Kashagan CC01 projects, SOCAR GPC (via Fluor);

- Technical Support Team Leader PDO Gas Directorate, CSU of many facilities in Oman gas system, production optimization & troubleshooting, Business Planning;

- Head of Commissioning Oman LNG Upstream Facilities;

- Head Omar Gas plant and Gas Transport System for AFPC Syria;

- Several supervisory jobs NAM (Coevorden Gas, Schoonebeek oil);

- Process engineer and Head of Laboratory and Quality Control at Kappa graphic board (pulp & paper).

