Main job highlights:
- study on optimizing partial abandonment of the field, this included giving engineered solutions and economic evaluation of the different options;
-study on reconnecting economic wells to existing production facilities from shut in reservoir blocks.

Responsibilities and accountabilities as supervisor for the Schoonebeek oil field:-production of 150.000 bbl/day gross crude;
- 80 prodcucers (gaslift, beampump, free flow), 40 water injectors, 4 steam injection wells;
-production and treatment of 200.000 Nm3/day sweet liftgas; 
-compression and export of 240.000 Nm3/day sour associated and liftgas;
-treatment of 1500 m3/day surface water to boiler feedwater quality, injection of 1200 ton/day of high pressure steam; 
-treatment of the oil to export specification, fiscalisation and loading of the oil;
-operation of associated emulsion, water, steam, sweet and high sour gas pipeline systems.

Liaise with maintenance sections on planning and safe execution of preventive and corrective maintenance to maintain integrity of process facilities. Designed and commissioned several projects to increase oil production (total 240 bbl/day). Accountable for an operating budget of NFI. 25.000.000, -. Number of staff 35. 

Special highlight : in charge of commissioning an extension of the high pressure steam injection project, inlcuding wells, plants, pipelines. Evaluate well performance, carry out planning programming, well interventions to optimize concerned production.
